<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05017i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05017i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05017i"> 17(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lough Neagh = Dead Sea</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The natives say that at low water they glimpse fragments of buildings and pillars rising out of the bottom of the lake. But this is only a fancy. Yet beneath the waters of the <mark>Dead Sea</mark> are thought to lie the Cities of the Plain. The northern part of the lake is very deep, the southern part very shallow.] <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Lot&apos;s Wife] 89</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: In Irish folklore there is imagined a city at the bottom of Lough Neagh in Ulster.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c02019j" href="c02all.htm#c02019j">VI.C.02:019(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
